  "local_port": 45780,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some recipes using 4 ounces of steak?",
  "response": "With 4 ounces of steak, you can create several delicious recipes. Here are a few ideas:\n\n### 1. **Steak Salad**\n- **Ingredients**: Mixed greens, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, feta cheese, balsamic vinaigrette.\n- **Instructions**: Grill or pan-sear the steak to your desired doneness. Slice thinly and arrange over a bed of mixed greens, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, and red onion. Sprinkle with feta cheese and drizzle with balsamic vinaigrette.\n\n### 2. **Steak Tacos**\n- **Ingredients**: Small tortillas, salsa, guacamole, shredded lettuce, shredded cheese, lime wedges.\n- **Instructions**: Season the steak with taco seasoning or your favorite spices. Grill or pan-sear the steak, then slice thinly. Serve on warm tortillas with salsa, guacamole, shredded lettuce, cheese, and a squeeze of lime.\n\n### 3. **Steak Sandwich**\n- **Ingredients**: Ciabatta or hoagie roll, caramelized onions, saut\u00e9ed mushrooms, provolone cheese, arugula, Dijon mustard.\n- **Instructions**: Grill or pan-sear the steak, then slice thinly. Assemble the sandwich with caramelized onions, saut\u00e9ed mushrooms, provolone cheese, and arugula on a toasted ciabatta or hoagie roll. Spread Dijon mustard on the bread for added flavor.\n\n### 4. **Steak and Eggs**\n- **Ingredients**: Eggs, butter, salt, pepper, toast or hash browns.\n- **Instructions**: Cook the steak to your desired doneness. In the same pan, fry or scramble eggs in butter. Serve the steak and eggs with toast or hash browns.\n\n### 5. **Steak Stir-Fry**\n- **Ingredients**: Mixed vegetables (bell peppers, broccoli, snap peas, carrots), soy sauce, garlic, ginger, sesame oil, rice or noodles.\n- **Instructions**: Slice the steak thinly and marinate in soy sauce, garlic, and ginger for 15-30 minutes. Stir-fry the vegetables in sesame oil until tender-crisp. Add the steak and cook until done. Serve over rice or noodles.\n\n### 6. **Steak and Blue Cheese Crostini**\n- **Ingredients**: Baguette slices, blue cheese, arugula, balsamic glaze.\n- **Instructions**: Grill or pan-sear the steak, then slice thinly. Toast baguette slices and top with blue cheese, arugula, and steak slices. Drizzle with balsamic glaze.\n\n### 7. **Steak and Mushroom Risotto**\n- **Ingredients**: Arborio rice, chicken or beef broth, mushrooms, onion, garlic, Parmesan cheese, white wine, butter.\n- **Instructions**: Cook the steak to your desired doneness, then slice thinly. In a separate pan, saut\u00e9 mushrooms, onion, and garlic. Add Arborio rice and toast slightly. Gradually add broth and white wine, stirring until the rice is creamy and cooked through. Stir in Parmesan cheese and butter. Serve the steak slices over the risotto.\n\nThese recipes allow you to make the most of 4 ounces of steak while complementing it with other flavorful ingredients.",
